com.intellij.util.xml

Annotation Type SubTag


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=METHOD)
public @interface SubTag
    Annotates DOM attribute children getters, that should return DomElement. The getters may be annotated with Convert annotation, if it returns GenericDomValue inheritor.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      int index 
      boolean indicator 
      java.lang.String value 

    • Element Detail

      • value

        public abstract java.lang.String value
        Returns:
        child XML tag name if it can't be inferred from the getter name (see NameStrategy)
        Default:
        ""

      • index

        public abstract int index
        Returns:
        if there are several child XML tags with the same name (e.g. always 2), the number of the child tag we should deal with
        Default:
        0

      • indicator

        public abstract boolean indicator
        Returns:
        for methods returning GenericDomValue<Boolean>, defines, whether the Boolean.TRUE should correspond just to empty tag existence, and Boolean.FALSE - to non-existence. index() should be always 0 in such a case.
        Default:
        false
